  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Sport Hotel Arabba is on a half board basis.</p>
<p>Start the day with a great breakfast spread of fresh breads, jams, yogurt, meat and pastries. There's also daily hot options including bacon and eggs. </p>
<p>For dinner, you'll get to choose from four courses. Expect hearty, traditional Tyrolean dishes complemented by over 700 labels of wine (drinks are payable locally). </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">With its warm hospitality, and its perfect mix of classic alpine décor and modern comforts, you'll instantly feel at home at the Sport Hotel Arabba. With a great location in Arabba, you can easily get on and off the slopes each day and when you return a lovely wellness area awaits. The hotel has a long tradition of welcoming British skiers, and is a favourite with our Inghams guests.</span></p>
<h2>Great Location</h2>
<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The hotel is in a prime location for accessing the Dolomites, with the Burz chairlift just over the road and the Porta Vescovo lift a short walk away. If you are looking to head over to <a data-udi="umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f5a15898b6694ef6a1c755346a0e1ba8}" title="Corvara &amp; Colfosco">Covara and Colfosco</a>,  La Villa and the Hidden Valley, head up the Burz lift. Head up the Porta Vescovo lift for the challenging runs in Arabba, <a data-udi="umb://document/4b1a446ce5904ac5997483a5477c9c8c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/4b1a446ce5904ac5997483a5477c9c8c}" title="Val di Fassa (Canazei, Campitello, Alba &amp; Penia)">Val d'Fassa</a> and the renowned Marmolada glacier. Whichever way you choose to go fantastic skiing is on your doorstep, and when you return, its</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> easy to ski back close to the hotel, where you'll have your own heated ski locker to store your equipment. </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">It's also a short walk from the centre of town if you want to explore more of the resort.</span></p>
<h2>Relaxation</h2>
<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">When you return from a day on the slopes, grab a drink from the bar and relax in front of the log fire or take some time to rejuvenate in the wellness are with two saunas, a Turkish bath and a large whirlpool, </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">or just relax on the comfortable loungers. Treat yourself to a massage or beauty treatment with the in-house therapists for the ultimate treat (pay locally). Stay active in the hotels fitness room with a range of equipment including weights and a variety of machines.</span></p>
<p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Start the day off at the varied breakfast buffet, and end your evening with a hearty four course evening meal. Before heading to bed, head to the bar for a digestif or a glass of wine - there are over 700 types of wine in the cellar.</span></p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
